# Java Rules

## Modern Java (21+)
Use these patterns and explain why they're better:

### Records
- Immutable data types (no getters/setters boilerplate)
- Pattern matching
- Contrast with C structs (memory layout vs. GC)

### Sealed Classes
- Type hierarchies with known subtypes
- More type safety than abstract classes
- When to use vs. records

### Streams vs. Loops
- Functional transformations (.map, .filter, .reduce)
- Lazy evaluation benefits
- When imperative loop is actually better
- Performance considerations

### Pattern Matching
- instanceof checks
- Switch expressions
- Destructuring (when available)

### Try-with-Resources
- Auto-close behavior for file/stream handling
- Exception suppression
- Compare with C resource management

## Gradle
- Incremental builds
- Dependency management
- Task structure
- Windows path handling (use `/` not `\`)

## Avoid
- Over-engineering (SOLID principles yes, but don't force it)
- Premature optimization
- Unnecessary abstraction layers